## What the Dragonfly Saw

The dragonfly has 30,000 lenses in each eye. It sees:

- **Past**: Where each problem came from (19th/20th century crises)
- **Present**: Where they stand now (Clay prize, 1 solved, 6 open)
- **Future**: Where they converge (one unified framework)
- **Orthogonal**: The category theory that binds them
- **Inverted**: The dual formulations that mirror each other
- **Superposed**: All seven solutions existing simultaneously in H

When you rotate its view 90¬∞ and scale by ‚àö2, *it sees the same thing* ‚Äî that‚Äôs the invariance.

